				<div style="width: 80%;" class="figure-inner">
						<a class="lightbox" href="/img/figure/figure2_5.jpg" data-title='Figure 2.5 Observed Sea Level Trends'>
							<picture>
		<source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/img/styles/figure2_5-1200.jpg, /img/styles/figure2_5-1200@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 992px)" srcset="/img/styles/figure2_5-992.jpg, /img/styles/figure2_5-992@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/img/styles/figure2_5-768.jpg, /img/styles/figure2_5-768@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="/img/styles/figure2_5-480.jpg, /img/styles/figure2_5-480@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 320px)" srcset="/img/styles/figure2_5-320.jpg, /img/styles/figure2_5-320@2x.jpg 2x">

								<img src="/img/figure/figure2_5.jpg"
									 alt="Observed Sea Level Trends" 
									class="big-img img-fluid"  
									aria-describedby="description-2-5"
								/>
							</picture>
						</a>
						<aside id="description-2-5" class="sr-only">A map shows sea level trends for the coastlines of the continental US, Hawai’i, and US Caribbean and across much of the Pacific and Atlantic Oceans for 1993 to 2020, as described in the text and caption. Shading shows trends across ocean areas while colored circles show trends at specific locations on the coast. A legend shows trends in inches per decade, ranging from decreases of 3 inches (dark blue) to increases of 4 inches (dark red). Text beneath the map reads: Global average: increase of 1.3 inches per decade; contiguous US average: increase of 1.8 inches per decade. Most of the Atlantic Ocean shows increases of 1 to 4 inches. Eastern and southern portions of the Pacific show trends of 0 to 1 inch, with larger increases of 1 to 3 inches across the central and western Pacific. Along the coastlines, Hawai’i and Puerto Rico generally show increases of 1 to 2 inches. Trends are positive along the US Atlantic and Gulf coasts, with rates generally 1 to 2 inches in the Northeast, and 2 to 4 inches elsewhere. Most of the Pacific coast of the contiguous US shows increases of 0 to 3 inches, but several locations in the Northwest show decreases of 0 to 1. The southern Alaska coast shows decreases of up to 3 inches, with mixed trends at other locations in the other parts of Alaska visible on the map.</aside>
				</div>
				

					<div class="caption"
						 data-href="/img/figure/figure2_5.jpg"
						 data-title='Figure 2.5 Observed Sea Level Trends'>
						<div class="intent">Sea levels are rising across most US coastal areas.</div>
						<span class="ordinal">Figure 2.5. </span>Satellite and tide gauge data show trends in sea level rise during 1993–2020 that are, on average, greater than global trends. Sea levels are not rising uniformly across US coastlines. The highest rates of sea level rise have occurred along the Gulf Coast and Atlantic Coast, with lower rates on the Pacific Coast and sea level fall along parts of the Alaska Coast. Rates of sea level rise in Hawai‘i and Puerto Rico are closer to the global average. Adapted from Sweet et al. 2022.<sup><a href='#fn:67' rel='footnote' onclick='return false;'>67</a></sup>
					</div>
	    </section> 
 






	

	<section id="art-78" class="artwork">
		<div class="artwork-title-bold" style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--tsu-cyan-blue)">Art &times; Climate</div>
		<div class="grid-row">
			<div class="grid-col-12 xtablet:grid-offset-1 tablet:grid-col-5 artwork-inner">
				<a class="lightbox" href="/img/art/Xavier_Cortada.jpg" data-title='Elevation Drive: 7 Feet Above Sea Level' style="display:inline-block;text-align:center">
					<picture>
		<source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="/img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-1200.jpg, /img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-1200@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 992px)" srcset="/img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-992.jpg, /img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-992@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="/img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-768.jpg, /img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-768@2x.jpg 2x">
		<source media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="/img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-480.jpg, /img/styles-art/Xavier_Cortada-480@2x.jpg 2x">
